docs.text: if first-time director hal salwen could shoot an entire movie of characters typing at their computers , he would .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: as it is , he settles for characters talking on the phone .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: denise calls up is a movie for and about the electronic generation , where characters are too caught up with their work and insecurities prefer to live out their relationships and fantasies on the phone .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it's a satire - and a sometimes funny one - about how we let handphones , call-waiting and answering machines run our lives .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the problem : denise calls up is a movie about an idea .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: a darn good one , but still an 80 minute-long idea .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and despite salwen's attempt at plots and sub-plots , despite some genuinely funny moments , you can predict the movie's outcome within the first fifteen minutes .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: you get the drift after a series of shots of characters explaining over the phone why they all couldn't make it for a party - nobody is going to be meeting anybody in this film , they would rather be talking on the phone .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: here's salwen's plot : while all the characters are in a dysfunctional , telefixated limbo , loud quirky stranger denise calls up martin to announce that she is pregnant with his child , courtesy of the sperm he donated to the local bank .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: as martin progresses from slamming the phone on her to long phone conversations over the baby's name , his friends - and his friends' friends - get involved , courtesy of call-waiting and double-lines .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: in the tigher and more tantalizing sub-plot , barbara and jerry are set up on a blind date that neither turns up for .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: both profess to have too complicated schedules to ever meet , but they get it going over the phone .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: with repeated phone sex comes a glitch ; what if the other person is simply faking it ?

docs.text: denise calls up scores with some inspired moments .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: mousy barbara metamorphoses into a vamp over her cordless , everyone shares the excitement of denise's delivery through a conference call to her handphone , and barbara's best friend gale is killed in a car accident while taling animatedly into another friend's answering machine .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: ( as gale's overly-chatty aunt recounts , her cordless was knicked into her ear and lodged in her brain . )

docs.text: but these moments are not enough to sustain the movie .
